---
// ExpertPageLayout can't render live inside the styleguide [slug] page — it
// wraps BaseLayout, which emits a full <html> document. This static preview
// describes the layout's chrome, slot, and composition pattern.
---

<div class="space-y-6">
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Chrome order</h3>
    <pre
      class="mt-2"
      style="background: var(--color-ink); color: var(--color-bg); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; white-space: pre-wrap;"
    >
{`ExpertPageLayout
└── BaseLayout
    ├── slot "schema"  ← buildPersonGraph(...) JSON-LD
    └── div.expert
        ├── header.expert__head
        │   ├── BreadcrumbBar
        │   └── div.expert__identity
        │       ├── img.expert__headshot   (optional)
        │       └── div.expert__namelock
        │           ├── p.expert__role     (mono caps eyebrow)
        │           └── PageHeading        (H1 + LastUpdatedDate)
        └── main.expert__main
            ├── section  About — bio <slot />
            ├── section  Credentials list
            ├── section  Pages reviewed     (optional)
            └── p.expert__linkedin          (optional)`}
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Pure-data archetype</h3>
    <p class="t-body mt-2" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px; max-width: 75ch;">
      Expert pages carry no bespoke composition. The <code>experts/[slug]</code>
      route reads a <code>pages-expert</code> content entry and passes the
      frontmatter straight in; the markdown body (the bio prose) flows into the
      default <code>&lt;slot /&gt;</code>. Add an expert by adding a content
      entry — no new route file.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Props</h3>
    <ul
      class="mt-3 space-y-0"
      style="border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-bg);"
    >
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 9rem;">title / description / canonical</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Head meta and schema identity.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 9rem;">name / role / credentials</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Feed buildPersonGraph (Person, jobTitle, knowsAbout).</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 9rem;">headshot / linkedin / pagesReviewed</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Optional. Portrait, sameAs link, and cross-references.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
